 Who we're looking for 
Toyota's Enterprise Strategy Department is looking for a passionate and highly motivated Economic Forecasting Manager. 
The primary responsibility of this role is to manage Toyota Motor North America's (TMNA) Macro Economic forecasts for the near, mid, and long term (2026 and beyond), as well as working with groups across the organization (including the executive level) that use these forecasts. These economic forecasts are a crucial element for TMNA's planning of vehicle lines, production footprint, and production planning, as well as headquarters planning, dealer operations, and many other areas. In addition to the scheduled projects, there are periodic ad hoc studies not only on Macroeconomic topics but also behavioral economics and similar factors that can drive customer behavior. 
Reporting to the Forecasting Manager, the person in this role will support the Enterprise Strategy Market Insights Department's objective to provide accurate and insightful forecasts to the organization for confident decision-making.
 What you'll be doing
 Develop and finalize the short, mid, and long-term U.S. economic outlook and possible scenarios to be reviewed and shared through TMNA Senior Management. 
 Apply modeling expertise to refine methodologies for forecasting the near to long-term outlook, for inclusion in forecasts & scenario planning. Responsible for identifying emerging economic issues and elevating to senior management with thought pieces. 
 Produce in-depth thematic studies to aid in research, forecasting, and scenario planning. 
 Support range of executive ad hoc requests related to economic topics. Analyze economic data releases and compile periodic reports, including quarterly economic monitor, monthly economic update for communications and sales team. 
 Collect, summarize, and formulate TMNA point of view regarding third-party economist views, through periodic and ad hoc Wall Street economist interviews and economic research conferences. 
 Consult with and advise internal stakeholders at all levels on economic issues and questions, providing subject matter expertise at all levels. 
 Maintain ongoing collaboration with counterparts in Japan, at Toyota Motor Corporation's Research Division. 
 Collaborate with other experts within TMNA and Toyota Financial Services (TFS). 
What you bring
 Bachelor's degree or higher in Economics is required. 
 Subject matter expertise in economic forecasting, including 5+ years of working experience and 3+ years of working with economic forecasts required. 
 Experience modeling economic impact on an industry or sector is required. 
 Ability to deal with both qualitative and quantitative data is required. 
 Ability to simplify and communicate complex topics into easily understandable terms is required. 
 Strong presentation skills and experience presenting to varied audiences including management is required. 
 Ability to knowledgeably interview Wall Street and other third-party economists, maintaining good rapport is required. 
Added bonus if you have
 Masters or Ph. D. in Economics is preferred. 
 Experience with process automation, big data, and/or AI integration is preferred. 
 An understanding of North American automotive markets is preferred. 
 Experience presenting to corporate senior management is preferred. 
 Experience with specialized economic software or models (Oxford Economics, Macro-Economic Advisors, etc.) is preferred. 
